Active Directory (AD)

Definition

Microsoft's centralized Identity and Access Management (IAM) service.

Manages:

Users

Computers

Groups

Authentication

Authorization

Security Policies



Purpose: Centralized management of enterprise identities and access.


---

Authentication vs Authorization

Authentication

Verifies identity.

"Who are you?"


Example:

Username + Password

Kerberos


Authorization

Determines permissions.

"What can you access?"


Example:

Shared Drive

Internal Application

Database



