---

NTLM

Older authentication protocol.

Characteristics:

Password challenge-response

Legacy support

Less secure

Vulnerable to attacks


Still exists because of legacy applications.


---

Kerberos

Modern authentication protocol.

Uses:

Ticket-based authentication

Single Sign-On (SSO)


Advantages:

More secure

Password not repeatedly transmitted

Faster enterprise authentication



