Key Takeaways

Active Directory is the foundation of enterprise identity.

Kerberos is preferred over NTLM because it uses secure ticket-based authentication.

Group Policy enforces security consistently across thousands of devices.

Replication keeps Domain Controllers synchronized.

AD is a high-value target because compromising it can provide broad access across the organization.

Enterprise security depends not only on technology but also on strong identity management, least privilege, continuous monitoring, and timely removal of unnecessary access.



